SIMPLE: hydrometrical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydrometrical
<hw>Hy`dro*met"ric*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>hydrom⟦egrave⟧trique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to an hydrometer, or to the determination of the specific
gravity of fluids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to measurement of the velocity,
discharge, etc., of running water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Made by means of an hydrometer; <as>as,
<ex>hydrometric</ex> observations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hydrometric pendulum</b></col>, <cd>a species of
hydrometer consisting of a hollow ball of ivory or metal suspended by a
treated from the center of a graduated quadrant, and held in a stream to
measure the velocity of the water by the inclination given to the
thread; a kind of current gauge.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydrometrograph</ent>⟦br⟧
